social_posts.post_text: It took 44 days but I finally had my first Tucker dream since he passed and I woke up crying. It’s wild how real they can feel, and oddly comforting at the same time. Sharing a happy video of one of his favorite things - riling Bear up after a walk and being very loud🤣 Tucker’s daily zoomies made me grateful that he never lost the puppy side of himself.
Finally something bigger than him🦄🦄🦄
He loves her!
It’s true, but I love him for it.
80° on Christmas Eve and we’re not complaining.
Merry Christmas, friends🎄
I think he’s pretty cute with any background.
My 2022 top 9 favorites because I didn’t love the actual one😬 Plus a bonus of the boys together.. those are what I miss the most.
It was a very breezy day.
Hello handsome.

Big annoyed I said No to getting on the couch after we both got soaked in the rain. I feel like we haven’t had this much rain at the beach in foreverrrr and having a 100lb fluffy dog is not making me enjoy it🥲
We’re here to tell you that it is *still* raining in LA. #sendmoretowels
He’s floating👼🏼

I’m late on the post (time still seems to be moving differently) but it’s Bear’s ‘gotcha anniversary😍 4 years of Bear. That first year was a handful but my gosh he was the cutest puppy I’ve ever seen.

Sometimes Bear does things that are so wholesome I’m caught off guard. This morning on a walk there were recycle bins blocking the side walk so he hopped off into the street. After we passed I said “back up, babe” and what I meant was “get back up onto the sidewalk” but what he heard was a cue I use when he’s hovering too close and I want space, “back up” aka back his body up and walk backwards🤣 after a long pause, he started walking backwards into my legs. It made me laugh. Love this kid so much.

Yesterday IG suggested I stitch these together to make this, and at first it made me cry. But after watching it through - it was a beautiful memory that made me happy. Grief still comes and goes in waves, this week I miss him a lot.
The cold wind is back and he couldn’t be more pleased.
We’re in our happy place🌵
Forever trying to save his pool toys from being sucked into the filter.
Waiting for me to throw something in the pool 🎾.
Goldens in golden hour light will forever be my favorite✨
He’s in a playful mood this morning.
Happy Saturday from a happy puppy.

Yesterday was (or would have been. I’m very bad at talking about him in past tense still) Tucker’s birthday. I had planned to share my favorite past birthday pictures in the morning here but so many emotions and tears to start the day. It’s still rough sometimes💔 I think about him a lot and am lucky to have the best of friends who also still think and talk about him a lot with me. He was so special. [the last two pictures are him at 9 weeks old and I swear it does not seem like that long ago]
Will only sit on the chairs and benches at the vet.

a June Hello from Mr.Bear🖤 I couldn’t pick one. He’s still the happiest pup and I think we’ve finally gotten allergies under control (well he’s still on long term antibiotics and those always solve our problems during the course). Im keeping my fingers crossed for more sunshine this month, gray May was not my favorite.
Teefies.
We’ve had (almost) nothing but grey skies for.ever. Here’s one magical moment of sun we got this month☀️
